<br>
With guides you need to understand that they aren't really paid and I know what it's like to have a shitty customer service job with people that expect more of you than you are allowed to do.  Just be glad we have them at all.  The guides take time out of their lives to do what they are limited to do to help you.  GMs are their own story... they get paid... which is at least in my opinion better off than the poor guides.  <br>
<br>
You all know that shit happens after patches.  And because of this they are more than likely bombarded the whole time.  You've gotta just be patient most of the time. It's not the guides fault Verant/Sony changed the way they have GMs deal with stuff...and it's not the GMs fault either.  They are just doing their job.  Now if they don't understand the differences of our server compared to others that's their own fault cause the info is out there.<br>
<br>
It's a game people.  There's no real reason to get so pissed off over a game.  Don't like the game?  Then leave... no one's keeping you here.  I just get upset when volunteer help gets dissed along with the paid help.  You've got a problem with the way Verant/Sony changed the amount of GMs we have or how they work, email and bitch them out.  Don't trash the GMs because their bosses haven't done their job right.  Get your friends to email and bitch too.  Who knows... it may or may not help... this is a company that in my opinion seems in it all for the money... lets see if they will listen to those that pay the money for the services they claim to offer us. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Giver of da juice (tm)</span><br>  Posts: 1007<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/29/02 3:40:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1470.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Re:Oh the Customer Support</span><hr size=1> GM's can get around the 3 hour rezz timer but it invovles some &quot;work&quot; for them to do it. I dont mean that to belittle them. There arent enough of them and frankly I think they feel overwhelmed at times.<br>
