<br>
Even more recently, VI added some bugs that permit people to use an exploit to get a permanent 3H corpse; ie. the rez-timer will always say 3H and never tick down.  If there are any changes to rez-time, likely it's due to VI trying to fix this bug.  BTW, you can't get xp back from multiple rez's on such a corpse; they're typically used for bind-sight hopping and rez/coth tricks at the high end to leap deep into a raid zone and bypass yard trash. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4>The Soapbox</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.9.5.7<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

